{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-chapter-level-2-chapter-level-2-tsx","path":"/topics/bowel-screening/how-this-topic-was-developed/evidence-exclusion-criteria/","result":{"pageContext":{"chapter":{"id":"592e5fe1-5908-581d-a2c0-67d92b643605","slug":"evidence-exclusion-criteria","fullItemName":"Evidence exclusion criteria","depth":2,"htmlHeader":"<!-- begin field f67c4e24-0b9e-4e5e-bc9a-a7f20187c85d --><h2>Evidence exclusion criteria</h2><!-- end field f67c4e24-0b9e-4e5e-bc9a-a7f20187c85d -->","summary":null,"htmlStringContent":"<!-- begin item f4105d9b-6d21-4396-bd92-a7f20187a3cf --><!-- begin field 926ef6b5-7745-4cb5-9d76-a7f20187c85d --><h2>Our policy</h2><!-- end field 926ef6b5-7745-4cb5-9d76-a7f20187c85d --><!-- begin field f5879fb1-100d-4120-bb72-a7f20187c85d --><p>Scoping a literature search, and reviewing the evidence for CKS is a methodical and systematic process that is carried out by the lead clinical author for each topic. Relevant evidence is gathered in order that the clinical author can make fully informed decisions and recommendations. It is important to note that some evidence may be excluded for a variety of reasons. These reasons may be applied across all CKS topics or may be specific to a given topic.</p><p>Studies identified during literature searches are reviewed to identify the most appropriate information to author a CKS topic, ensuring any recommendations are based on the best evidence. We use the principles of the GRADE and PICOT approaches to assess the quality of published research. We use the principles of AGREE II to assess the quality of published guidelines.</p><!-- end field f5879fb1-100d-4120-bb72-a7f20187c85d --><!-- begin field 12a7bcc7-24a8-4f91-bde1-a7f20187c85d --><h2>Standard exclusions for scoping literature:</h2><!-- end field 12a7bcc7-24a8-4f91-bde1-a7f20187c85d --><!-- begin field 947687f8-28bf-4f83-8b7d-a7f20187c85d --><ul><li>Animal studies</li><li>Original research is not written in English</li></ul><!-- end field 947687f8-28bf-4f83-8b7d-a7f20187c85d --><!-- begin field d9c484b8-d25b-4d39-a47d-a7f20187c85d --><h2>Possible exclusions for reviewed literature:</h2><!-- end field d9c484b8-d25b-4d39-a47d-a7f20187c85d --><!-- begin field a0284ef3-44fc-4f61-8c18-a7f20187c85d --><ul><li>Sample size too small or study underpowered</li><li>Bias evident or promotional literature</li><li>Population not relevant</li><li>Intervention/treatment not relevant</li><li>Outcomes not relevant</li><li>Outcomes have no clear evidence of clinical effectiveness</li><li>Setting not relevant</li><li>Not relevant to UK</li><li>Incorrect study type</li><li>Review article</li><li>Duplicate reference</li></ul><!-- end field a0284ef3-44fc-4f61-8c18-a7f20187c85d --><!-- end item f4105d9b-6d21-4396-bd92-a7f20187a3cf -->","topic":{"id":"3ce0939c-7050-5776-a27a-f61be0cde1ee","topicId":"82504955-0e84-433e-bad4-93b1ed97ce03","topicName":"Bowel screening","slug":"bowel-screening","lastRevised":"Last revised in May 2019","chapters":[{"id":"bc2d7627-8fa0-5266-9a00-e712c6e2d181","fullItemName":"Summary","slug":"summary","subChapters":[]},{"id":"ab7b5b81-4eeb-53d8-a024-9a25103a6bb9","fullItemName":"Have I got the right topic?","slug":"have-i-got-the-right-topic","subChapters":[]},{"id":"b6c6aff8-902e-5f92-9bcc-c86051bf35e9","fullItemName":"How up-to-date is this topic?","slug":"how-up-to-date-is-this-topic","subChapters":[{"id":"5a4a85ce-0817-5737-a4bd-b21e5f4d471d","slug":"changes","fullItemName":"Changes"},{"id":"e84f94a1-b8f1-52c2-89c5-fe98e969d445","slug":"update","fullItemName":"Update"}]},{"id":"f993604e-d9e1-5f3d-a163-a694e0eec778","fullItemName":"Goals and outcome measures","slug":"goals-outcome-measures","subChapters":[{"id":"31c9b8f0-2cc3-51a8-8121-02bedaa57461","slug":"goals","fullItemName":"Goals"},{"id":"82451698-7794-505f-b671-4e02d8d0007c","slug":"outcome-measures","fullItemName":"Outcome measures"},{"id":"33e248f5-b211-5eca-9cdf-aff8271e67a6","slug":"audit-criteria","fullItemName":"Audit crite